'This isn't easy, these are dogs that are part of our family,' Joseph Giannini, the owner of Urban Out Sitters, told the Chicago Tribune.

'Everybody's very concerned for the safety of their dogs ... everybody's devastated.'

The van was taken shortly before 4pm, with the men, who were armed, ordering the driver out of the van, a 2002 Silver Chrysler Town and Country, and driving off.

'They ordered him out of the car, they hopped in the car and took off,' said Giannini. 

'Nobody was hurt, just shaken up.'

The dogs were all in the back of the van in cages.

